  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Consolidating Territory of Indigenous Guarani Communities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Native Community Territory (TCO) of Charagua Norte is located in the Chaco region in the Department of Santa Cruz. Several indigenous Guaran&#xED; communities live within the territory, which covers 269,878 acres. Though legally recognized, the territory must be resettled due to threats from non-indigenous people to take the land. This project will support the planned resettlement of 150 families, who will create five new indigenous communities. Heifer will provide technical training equipment, basic inputs and sheep for the establishment of traditional agricultural production systems; and, will help with organizational strengthening to create stable communities that occupy the territory in a planned manner and where there is equitable access to the natural resources on the part of indigenous men and women. The project will also promote advocacy before municipal and departmental governmental institutions for the establishment of public policies and to obtain public investment in favor of the communities. Passing on the gift will benefit an additional 120 indigenous families with seeds and the offspring of the sheep.</narrative>
  </description>
